    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with significant firepower, headlined by **Kyle Tucker** (85.72) and **Gunnar Henderson** (83.18), our two most efficient starts. **Kyle Tucker** benefits from an elite matchup against Ryan Feltner, carrying a strong xwOBA (0.372) and a favorable park factor (+14%) that elevates him to the top of our priority list. While **Gunnar Henderson** boasts an impressive score, we are monitoring a 31% rain risk in his contest, though his batting order position (#1) and platoon advantage make him a mandatory start despite the weather threat. We also see high-ceiling value in **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (74.56) and **Andy Pages** (73.82), both of whom are leveraged by advantageous platoon splits and pitcher delivery speeds that favor our aggressive stolen base strategy.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench involved **Nasim Nunez** (60.21), who posted a respectable efficiency score but ultimately yielded to the depth of our outfield and utility slots. While **Nasim Nunez** provides the necessary speed metrics we covet, the projection gap between him and starters like **Josh Lowe** (72.21)\u2014who benefits from a plus-matchup against Germ\u00e1n M\u00e1rquez\u2014was simply too wide to justify pulling a starter. Elsewhere, we are proceeding with caution regarding **Jackson Merrill** (55.56), as he faces a tougher challenge against Yusei Kikuchi and a strong defensive catcher behind the dish. While **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (67.48) remains a reliable play, we acknowledge the high skill level of Zac Gallen, keeping expectations tempered for his production today.",
